## Hey, I just made a Pull Request!

This PR introduces a new `ToastApi` for displaying rich toast notifications in the new frontend system, along with a modern `ToastDisplay` component that replaces `AlertDisplay` from `@backstage/core-components`.

### Why a new API?

After discussing with @Rugvip, we decided to introduce a dedicated `ToastApi` rather than extending the existing `AlertApi`. The key differences that warranted a new API:

- **Props structure**: Toast uses `title` + `description` whereas Alert uses a single `message`
- **Status values**: Toast uses `status` ('info' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'danger') vs Alert's `severity`
- **Timeout control**: Toast allows each notification to specify its own `timeout`, whereas Alert uses a global `transient` display mode
- **Additional features**: Toast supports action links, and programmatic dismissal

### Deprecation of AlertApi

`AlertApi` is now deprecated and will be removed in a future release. Deprecation warnings have been added to:

- `alertApiRef` in `@backstage/core-plugin-api`
- `alertApiRef` in `@backstage/frontend-plugin-api`
- `AlertApiForwarder` in `@backstage/core-app-api`

When using `AlertApi`, developers will see console warnings guiding them to migrate to `ToastApi`.

### Migration Path

The `ToastDisplay` component subscribes to **both** `ToastApi` and `AlertApi`, providing a seamless migration path:

- Existing code using `AlertApi` continues to work unchanged
- New code can adopt `ToastApi` for richer notifications
- Both APIs can be used side-by-side until `AlertApi` is fully deprecated

#### Migration Guide

| AlertApi                                     | ToastApi                                    |
| -------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `message: string`                            | `title: ReactNode`                          |
| `severity: 'error'`                          | `status: 'danger'`                          |
| `severity: 'success' \| 'info' \| 'warning'` | `status: 'success' \| 'info' \| 'warning'`  |
| `display: 'transient'`                       | `timeout: 5000` (or custom ms)              |
| `display: 'permanent'`                       | omit `timeout`                              |
| `post()` returns `void`                      | `post()` returns `string` (key for dismiss) |

#### Example Migration

```typescript
// Before (AlertApi) - DEPRECATED
import { alertApiRef, useApi } from '@backstage/core-plugin-api';

const alertApi = useApi(alertApiRef);
alertApi.post({
  message: 'Entity saved successfully',
  severity: 'success',
  display: 'transient',
});

// After (ToastApi)
import { toastApiRef, useApi } from '@backstage/frontend-plugin-api';

const toastApi = useApi(toastApiRef);
toastApi.post({
  title: 'Entity saved successfully',
  status: 'success',
  timeout: 5000,
});
```

### Usage

```typescript
import { toastApiRef, useApi } from '@backstage/frontend-plugin-api';

const toastApi = useApi(toastApiRef);

// Full-featured toast
toastApi.post({
  title: 'Entity saved',
  description: 'Your changes have been saved successfully.',
  status: 'success',
  timeout: 5000,
  links: [{ label: 'View entity', href: '/catalog/entity' }],
});

// Simple toast
toastApi.post({ title: 'Processing...', status: 'info' });

// Programmatic dismiss
const key = toastApi.post({ title: 'Uploading...', status: 'info' });
// Later...
toastApi.close(key);
```

